UngroupedDialogues.Text:
You know, Karl, you remind me of someone…
Or something…

<NextDialogue>k__BackingField.Text:
My childhood. Back when I hadn’t yet met you and still felt happiness.
It was also because my parents were still alive.
They really liked to barbeque, too…

They were fighting so much, they were always trying to grill each other. 
They got really clever with it. And they got huge barbeque tongs just for that, and trained in gym to be able to pick them up.

I still remember them running around with the huge barbeque tongs, trying to kill each other…
All the traps around the house…
But then, they went to marriage counsellor.
